<reference id="audience" xml:lang="en-us">
   <title>
      <keyword>audience</keyword>
   </title>
   <shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>audience</keyword>&gt; metadata element indicates,
through the value of its type attribute, the intended audience for a topic.
Since a topic can have multiple audiences, you can include multiple audience
elements. For each audience you specify, you can identify the high-level task
(<i>
         
         
         <keyword>job</keyword>
      
      
      </i>) they are trying to accomplish and the level
of experience (<i>
         
         
         <keyword>experiencelevel</keyword>
      
      
      </i>) expected.</shortdesc>
